# CertifyMe Full Stack Assessment

## Tech Stack

- Flask (Backend)
- SQLite (Database)
- HTML/CSS/JS (Frontend)

## Features

- Admin Signup & Login
- Forgot Password (token-based)
- Session-based Authentication
- Create, View, Edit, Delete Opportunities
- Data Persistence
- User-specific Data Isolation

## API Endpoints

### Auth APIs

- `POST /api/auth/signup` - Create admin account (requires email validation, 8+ char password)
- `POST /api/auth/login` - Login with email & password
- `POST /api/auth/forgot-password` - Request password reset (token expires in 1 hour)
- `GET /api/auth/me` - Get current logged-in admin info
- `POST /api/auth/logout` - Logout

### Opportunity APIs (Authenticated)

- `GET /api/opportunities` - List all opportunities for logged-in admin
- `GET /api/opportunities/<id>` - Get single opportunity by ID
- `POST /api/opportunities` - Create new opportunity
- `PUT /api/opportunities/<id>` - Update existing opportunity
- `DELETE /api/opportunities/<id>` - Delete opportunity

## Backend Implementation Status ✅

All required endpoints implemented with proper:

- ✅ HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- ✅ Status codes (200, 201, 400, 401, 404, 409)
- ✅ JSON responses
- ✅ Authentication validation
- ✅ Data isolation (each admin sees only their data)
- ✅ Email format validation
- ✅ Password minimum length (8 characters)
- ✅ Password reset tokens with 1-hour expiry
- ✅ CORS support for session-based auth

See `BACKEND_FIXES_EXPLAINED.md` for detailed explanation of all fixes.

## How to Run

### Easy Method (Batch Files)

**Option 1: Double-click the batch files**

1. Double-click `run-backend.bat` (starts backend on http://127.0.0.1:5000)
2. Double-click `run-frontend.bat` in another window (starts frontend on http://localhost:8000)
3. Open browser to **http://localhost:8000**

### Manual Method (Command Line)

#### Backend (Terminal 1)

```powershell
cd backend
C:\Users\AKASH\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python313\python.exe -m pip install -r requirements.txt
C:\Users\AKASH\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python313\python.exe app.py
```

The backend will start on **http://127.0.0.1:5000**

#### Frontend (Terminal 2)

```powershell
cd frontend
C:\Users\AKASH\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python313\python.exe -m http.server 8000
```

Open in browser: **http://localhost:8000**

## Database

- SQLite is used
- Database is created automatically when the backend runs

## Notes

- No UI changes were made as per instructions
- All data is stored in the database (no hardcoded data)
- Each admin can only access their own opportunities
